1500:Yua barely moved.[%p]
1600:All she did was sit on the sofa. Occasionally, she would stand up for a little, or change how she sat, but nothing more.[%p]
1700:And the whole time, she kept whispering. It amazed me that she could talk so much.[%p]
1800:She didn't call or text anyone, or use the computer to kill time. She didn't sleep. All she did was ask me questions. The words themselves were starting to lose their meaning.[%p]
1900:I hated being stared at.[%p]
2000:Shogun's mind reading, at least, only happened once in a while. I hated it, but it wasn't unbearable.[%p]
2100:But having Yua watch my every action with her expressionless, cold eyes... that felt like it was striking a fatal blow at the very core of who I was.[%p]
2200:As long as I was tied up here, unable to move, I couldn't see anything changing.[%p]
2300:I'd lost track of how long I'd been tied up.[%p]
2400:I had no idea how many days it had been.[%p]
2500:It felt like it might've only been two days, but it also might've been a month.[%p]
2600:Not being able to move was really stressful. For the past several hours, I'd thought of nothing but how I wanted to see a clock. I couldn't think of anything else.[%p]
